            <TextView
                android:id="@+id/textView14"
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="432dp"
                android:text="In a large pot, add enough water to cover the beef shank. Bring to a boil.

Add the beef shank and let it boil for about 10 minutes. Skim off any scum and impurities that rise to the surface.

Lower the heat to a simmer. Add the onion and garlic to the pot. Continue simmering until the beef is tender, which may take about 2 to 3 hours. You can also use a pressure cooker to speed up the process.

Once the beef is tender, add the corn on the cob, potatoes, and saba bananas. Continue simmering until the vegetables are cooked.

Season the broth with fish sauce or salt and pepper to taste. Adjust according to your preference.

Just before serving, add the pechay and cook for a few minutes until the leaves are wilted.

Serve hot, garnished with chopped green onions. Bulalo is typically enjoyed with steamed rice and fish sauce with calamansi (Filipino lime) on the side."
